{
  "texts": [
    "The first grade is the final exam grade, which reflects the comprehensive learning outcomes of the student for the entire semester and can be considered a summative evaluation.",
    "The second part is the regular grade, which takes into account classroom performance, coursework, and other factors, and captures the student's performance during the learning process.",
    "The first half of the reading material was the same for both groups: \"All optional courses' scores at your university consist of a regular grade and a final exam grade.",
    "The final exams are all objective questions with standard answers; the regular grades are given entirely by the teacher of the course. \"",
    "\"All optional courses' scores at your university consist of a regular grade and a final exam grade."
  ]
}